WEBVTT

00:03.496 --> 00:05.370
Hey!

00:05.549 --> 00:07.427
Come here. Welcome back.

00:07.428 --> 00:08.395
Thank you.

00:08.396 --> 00:09.529
- Here, this one's fresh.
- Thanks.

00:09.530 --> 00:11.298
- Oh, look at you.
- Oh, I had a corner, so...

00:11.299 --> 00:12.566
No, he's lying. I had the corner.

00:12.567 --> 00:14.067
It's fine. I had a huge breakfast.

00:14.068 --> 00:15.368
Come on, we want to see

00:15.369 --> 00:16.570
more pictures of Joanna.

00:16.571 --> 00:18.004
I've sent you so many already.

00:18.005 --> 00:19.206
But since you asked...

00:19.207 --> 00:21.007
Oh, here, I'll hold your coffee.

00:21.008 --> 00:22.809
Thank you.

00:22.810 --> 00:24.845
Wow, a lot of changes since I was gone.

00:24.846 --> 00:26.113
Congratulations, boss.

00:26.114 --> 00:29.182
Don't be ridiculous.
Blake is still the boss.

00:29.183 --> 00:30.884
Is Kat Sandoval here?

00:30.885 --> 00:32.786
Oh, she's in California
wrapping up her exit strategy

00:32.787 --> 00:34.788
from the avocado farm.
She'll be here next week.

00:34.789 --> 00:35.722
But we like her?

00:35.723 --> 00:37.424
I mean, I've heard some things.

00:37.425 --> 00:38.558
She meditates now.

00:38.559 --> 00:40.360
I get it. I breastfeed now.

00:40.361 --> 00:42.796
Oh, fun fact: when your body
detects warmer temperature,

00:42.797 --> 00:44.598
it'll change the content
of your breast milk

00:44.599 --> 00:46.266
to provide more hydration for your baby.

00:46.267 --> 00:48.535
I don't know how I know
that. Wow, that is a cute kid.

00:48.536 --> 00:49.536
Oh!

00:49.537 --> 00:50.737
Oh!

00:50.738 --> 00:52.038
Oh, look at those eyes.

00:52.039 --> 00:53.273
You are in so much trouble.

00:53.274 --> 00:54.741
I know, right?

00:54.742 --> 00:59.356
I could do this all day, but we
have a Women Transform the World

00:59.357 --> 01:00.418
- conference to plan.
- Yes.

01:00.419 --> 01:01.890
- Yes.
- And it ain't gonna plan itself.

01:01.891 --> 01:03.350
Oh! That's how I know that.

01:03.351 --> 01:04.650
Listen, you.

01:04.652 --> 01:06.433
As glad as I am

01:06.434 --> 01:08.301
to have you back, I want to remind you

01:08.302 --> 01:10.103
you still have a week
left on your maternity.

01:10.104 --> 01:12.572
I really wanted to be here
for the women's conference.

01:12.573 --> 01:14.360
Something about having
a little woman of my own

01:14.361 --> 01:15.694
made it even more important.

01:15.695 --> 01:17.696
But it is weird being
away from my daughter

01:17.697 --> 01:19.932
so I can make the world
better for my daughter.

01:19.933 --> 01:21.600
Still working on that balance.

01:21.601 --> 01:24.436
Well, that's what grandparents are for.

01:24.437 --> 01:25.904
Have Joe's parents seen Joanna?

01:25.905 --> 01:28.474
I haven't actually told them yet.

01:28.475 --> 01:29.842
Oh.

01:29.843 --> 01:30.839
I'm not avoiding it.

01:30.840 --> 01:32.841
I just got superstitious
when I was pregnant.

01:32.842 --> 01:35.115
I mean, I kept thinking this
poor woman just lost her son.

01:35.116 --> 01:36.711
What if something happens to this baby?

01:36.712 --> 01:37.812
How horrible will that be?

01:37.813 --> 01:39.014
Then, since Joanna was born,

01:39.015 --> 01:41.483
I've been completely
overwhelmed, but I will call.

01:41.484 --> 01:42.517
- Today.
- Good.

01:42.518 --> 01:43.918
As soon as I get a minute.

01:43.919 --> 01:46.721
And a caffeine rush, which
I will totally pump and dump.

01:46.722 --> 01:48.490
Let me know when I'm over-sharing.

01:48.491 --> 01:50.291
I've been alone with
a baby for a long time.

01:50.292 --> 01:52.861
As a rule, just pull back
when you feel yourself

01:52.862 --> 01:56.498
wanting to share color
or texture of anything.

01:56.499 --> 01:57.699
Thanks, ma'am.

01:57.700 --> 01:59.367
Sorry, you're being
summoned to the Sit Room.

01:59.368 --> 02:01.369
All right. Tell Jay
to start the meeting.

02:01.370 --> 02:02.804
Yeah.

02:02.805 --> 02:05.006
Operation Tiger Claw

02:05.007 --> 02:06.641
launches in four days, General.

02:06.642 --> 02:08.743
Is that sufficient time
to finish preparations?

02:08.744 --> 02:10.245
Ample time, Mr. President.

02:10.246 --> 02:12.180
Marines, Army, including Special Forces,

02:12.181 --> 02:15.083
as well as several British
and Canadian battalions

02:15.084 --> 02:16.584
are readying as we speak.

02:16.585 --> 02:17.852
What about air support?

02:17.853 --> 02:19.320
Taliban forces

02:19.321 --> 02:20.922
are concentrated in Baghlan Province,

02:20.923 --> 02:22.323
just outside Kabul.

02:22.324 --> 02:25.827
Air strikes could put the Afghan
civilians at a greater risk.

02:25.828 --> 02:27.362
While boots on the ground

02:27.363 --> 02:30.432
almost certainly means
more American casualties.

02:30.433 --> 02:32.500
Despite these concerns,

02:32.501 --> 02:34.969
we're confident this is the
best and most decisive way

02:34.970 --> 02:36.538
to decapitate the Taliban leadership.

02:36.539 --> 02:38.540
And send a clear message to Russia.

02:38.541 --> 02:42.610
Propping up the Taliban
in an effort to destabilize

02:42.611 --> 02:45.447
the Afghan central government
won't be tolerated anymore.

02:45.448 --> 02:49.484
Which is why, despite our
significant show of force,

02:49.485 --> 02:53.855
we will be following the Afghan
army's lead here, General.

02:53.856 --> 02:55.723
In the end, it's their fight.

02:55.724 --> 02:57.192
None of this will matter

02:57.193 --> 02:58.693
if we don't also lay the groundwork

02:58.694 --> 03:02.063
for a credible and
effective Afghan government.

03:02.064 --> 03:04.099
I mean, that is, if our end goal

03:04.100 --> 03:06.601
is still to withdraw
U.S. troops completely.

03:06.602 --> 03:09.270
That is our goal, of course.

03:09.271 --> 03:13.373
And a decisive blow would
help us achieve just that.

03:14.776 --> 03:15.977
General Mackey.

03:15.978 --> 03:18.675
Operation Tiger Claw could
take a significant bite

03:18.676 --> 03:19.886
out of the Taliban's control,

03:19.887 --> 03:21.883
while simultaneously setting the stage

03:21.884 --> 03:24.518
for lasting stability in Afghanistan.

03:26.221 --> 03:27.422
Right.

03:27.423 --> 03:29.823
Let's get it done.

03:32.760 --> 03:36.863
Peace through strength.
It's the party line.

03:39.000 --> 03:40.935
Give me some good news, people.

03:40.936 --> 03:43.071
Molly's returned from maternity leave.

03:43.072 --> 03:44.005
Molly, hey.

03:44.006 --> 03:46.007
Welcome back. We missed you.

03:46.008 --> 03:47.509
It's good to be back, Dr. McCord.

03:47.510 --> 03:49.344
The guys were just about to catch me up.

03:49.345 --> 03:51.312
So Senator Beau
Carpenter is behind bars.

03:51.313 --> 03:52.981
His replacement has been fully vetted,

03:52.982 --> 03:55.049
so our immediate intel leak is over.

03:55.050 --> 03:56.751
If only we had anything worth bringing

03:56.752 --> 03:58.274
to the Senate Intelligence Committee.

03:58.275 --> 03:59.254
Okay, look.

03:59.255 --> 04:01.589
Operation Tiger Claw
launches in four days.

04:01.590 --> 04:03.892
Our job is to collect
as much intel as possible

04:03.893 --> 04:05.602
on Russian and Taliban activities.

04:05.603 --> 04:07.840
The problem is our most
promising Russian assets

04:07.841 --> 04:09.148
in the region have gone to ground.

04:09.149 --> 04:10.916
They got spooked when
Osip Bakunin was murdered.

04:10.917 --> 04:12.885
Not Matvey Sokolov.

04:12.886 --> 04:14.153
Oh, that's your old friend

04:14.154 --> 04:16.411
from the Russian
Military Academy, right?

04:16.411 --> 04:17.423
Mm-hmm.

04:17.423 --> 04:19.425
Uh...

04:19.426 --> 04:20.593
Yeah, his profile is perfect.

04:20.594 --> 04:23.596
GRU spy working as a
liaison to the Taliban.

04:23.597 --> 04:25.030
Yeah, when I knew him,

04:25.031 --> 04:27.032
Matvey had deep ideological
issues with Russia

04:27.033 --> 04:28.901
and the way we meddled
in foreign governments,

04:28.902 --> 04:31.103
particularly Afghanistan.

04:31.104 --> 04:33.305
Plus, he's a sucker
for anything Western.

04:33.306 --> 04:35.007
He used to wear Van Halen T-shirts

04:35.008 --> 04:36.175
under his combat uniform.

04:36.176 --> 04:38.811
Dylan, you've been
running point on this.

04:38.812 --> 04:39.879
What's your impression?

04:39.880 --> 04:41.013
That he's not reliable.

04:41.014 --> 04:42.548
His information about leadership changes

04:42.549 --> 04:43.949
in the Taliban were solid,

04:43.950 --> 04:46.502
and he did tell you that there
were more where that came from.

04:46.503 --> 04:47.965
But every time I try to close the deal,

04:47.966 --> 04:49.138
he asks for something different.

04:49.139 --> 04:50.306
I can't get him over the finish line.

04:50.307 --> 04:51.707
We could try something else.

04:51.708 --> 04:54.510
Stop offering him things and
put a little pressure on him.

04:54.511 --> 04:57.013
Tell him he's running out
of time to be useful to us.

04:57.014 --> 04:59.849
Or... I could talk to him.

04:59.850 --> 05:01.717
Doesn't he believe

05:01.718 --> 05:03.019
Dmitri Petrov is dead?

05:03.020 --> 05:04.787
And what better way to convince a man

05:04.788 --> 05:06.656
that the United States
government can be trusted

05:06.657 --> 05:09.325
than to reveal that they
rescued me from the gulag

05:09.326 --> 05:11.327
and saved my life?

05:11.328 --> 05:13.062
When I knew him, America was his dream.

05:13.063 --> 05:14.530
And what if he has a new dream?

05:14.531 --> 05:17.004
You could wind up back in
witness protection or worse.

05:17.005 --> 05:19.469
I do not believe he would burn me.

05:19.470 --> 05:21.537
M-Matvey Sokolov is a Russian spy

05:21.538 --> 05:22.939
who is embedded with the Taliban.

05:22.940 --> 05:25.775
I have to at least try to
convince him to work with us.

05:25.776 --> 05:27.310
It's a huge risk.

05:27.311 --> 05:28.578
And you have taught me, sir,

05:28.579 --> 05:30.379
that those are the
only ones worth taking.

05:33.383 --> 05:34.817
Okay.

05:34.818 --> 05:38.421
Get in touch with Sokolov,
tell him I want to meet.

05:38.422 --> 05:40.722
We'll leave for Kabul tonight.

05:47.959 --> 05:49.799
_

05:52.936 --> 05:57.386
_

05:57.387 --> 05:59.309
