08:01.586 --> 08:05.223
Hello? Is this Mrs. Garcia?

08:05.224 --> 08:06.991
My name is Daisy Grant.

08:06.992 --> 08:09.461
You don't know me, but I knew your son.

08:09.462 --> 08:11.930
I knew Joe.

08:11.931 --> 08:14.232
Ma'am, I'm so sorry to bother you here.

08:14.233 --> 08:17.368
No, no, no, I just had to get my 30...

08:17.369 --> 08:18.636
25 minutes in.

08:18.637 --> 08:20.371
I could hear my Fitbit screaming at me

08:20.372 --> 08:23.641
from whatever drawer I shoved it in.

08:23.642 --> 08:25.610
How's your first day back going?

08:25.611 --> 08:27.846
Fine. Great.

08:27.847 --> 08:32.049
I mean, I miss her, but...
I'm talking to adults,

08:32.051 --> 08:33.885
I'm using my brain, and
I'm so happy to be back

08:33.885 --> 08:36.121
for the women's conference,
because, as we discussed,

08:36.121 --> 08:37.355
the fact that I have a daughter now

08:37.356 --> 08:39.090
makes all of these issues
even more important.

08:39.091 --> 08:41.126
So I don't at all
regret at all coming back

08:41.126 --> 08:43.044
- from maternity leave early.
- Good.

08:43.044 --> 08:44.496
Because, you know, it's
a privilege to have a job

08:44.497 --> 08:45.930
where there is maternity leave.

08:45.931 --> 08:48.433
But the thing is,

08:48.434 --> 08:50.502
I finally talked to Joe's mother.

08:50.503 --> 08:52.804
And she was so happy to hear from me,

08:52.805 --> 08:55.039
and she really wants to meet Joanna.

08:55.040 --> 08:56.875
And I feel like I can't say no to her

08:56.876 --> 08:59.878
because I'm the one who
contacted her out of the blue.

08:59.879 --> 09:02.914
And they live in Connecticut,
which is, like, a long drive.

09:02.915 --> 09:04.816
So, you know, the whole
thing is gonna be a lot,

09:04.817 --> 09:07.218
and I know that I just got back,

09:07.219 --> 09:09.920
but I need to ask for a day off.

09:12.991 --> 09:14.791
Daisy...

09:16.928 --> 09:18.663
...take two days off.

09:18.664 --> 09:20.765
Really?

09:20.766 --> 09:22.734
Take as many days as you need.

09:22.735 --> 09:25.136
Oh, God, I feel like I'm gonna cry.

09:25.137 --> 09:28.573
Yeah, you're gonna have to
get used to that feeling.

09:31.709 --> 09:33.978
I'm just saying,

09:33.979 --> 09:38.783
Afghanistan, 72 hours before

09:38.784 --> 09:42.220
a massive U.S. military operation.

09:42.221 --> 09:45.123
I mean, if you need an adrenaline rush,

09:45.124 --> 09:47.025
why don't you just, I don't know,

09:47.026 --> 09:49.761
stay home and take up race car driving?

09:49.762 --> 09:51.830
Our troops are about to go toe to toe

09:51.831 --> 09:53.464
against the Taliban rebels.

09:53.465 --> 09:54.933
Don't you think it'd be a good idea

09:54.934 --> 09:57.302
to have as much on-the-ground
intel as possible?

09:57.303 --> 10:00.170
Could I have that green one, please?

10:02.040 --> 10:04.008
Are you really confident
that Alexander can

10:04.009 --> 10:06.845
get this Russian operative to talk?

10:06.846 --> 10:08.513
Well, if his old friend
is who he says he is,

10:08.514 --> 10:12.450
I'll come back with information
about Taliban troop movements

10:12.451 --> 10:14.719
that could prove invaluable.

10:14.720 --> 10:18.156
Okay, literally, all I could make out

10:18.157 --> 10:21.359
from that sentence were
the words "I'll come back".

10:21.360 --> 10:23.795
Everything else just sounded
like Charlie Brown's teacher.

10:23.796 --> 10:26.731
What do you want me to do, babe?

10:26.732 --> 10:31.703
Please say it again... and mean it.

10:31.704 --> 10:35.539
I'll come back. I promise.

10:37.408 --> 10:39.377
In the meantime, why don't you look into

10:39.378 --> 10:42.245
that race car driving thing?

